Anyways, it's funny to hear all this talk of countries using nuclear weapons to threaten each other and what not.  Considering that multiple countries have nuclear weapons and haven't used them in almost 60 years now.  These band-aid solutions may win support for a couple of years but to think that U.S. can keep nuclear weapons out of the hands of other countries forever is just wishful thinking.<br>
<br>
Eventually, Iraq will have nuclear weapons regardless if U.S. attacks them or not, and then you will have to deal with even bigger problems.  I say end the hostilities now and try to build bridges for the future.  I was actually toying with the idea of one term limits for American presidents so they couldnt pull these dumbass stunts so they could secure support for a second term.<br>
