<br>
   Merton keeps tossing around the &quot;soveriegn nation&quot; clause as to why any nation should be openly allowed to build anykinds of weapons that they want without fear of any sanctioning by the other countries of the world.   Merton, the fact you actually live in such an isolated Ivorty Tower to actually believe this makes it almost pointless to even argue with you.   How can you justify allowing a country led by a madman,  a man who during the war in 1991 lauched numerous missles arbitrarily into Israeal just to turn his invasion of kuwait into a holy war and get the other arab nations to support him?    <br>
<br>
    Sure merton, this is just the kind of guy you want with a freaking nuclear missle in his hands.   God forbid but if that day ever comes where saddamn  or any other deranged leader of a country attains one and launches it at the United States, Israeal, or anyone else who happens to piss him off , you can sit back in your chair in Chicago waiting for the shockwave to disentigrate you and think &quot;well he is perfectly in his right to have that bomb because he is the leader of a soveriegn nation&quot;.<br>
<br>
     This is exactly why such policing of the world is done by the U.N.  not just the United States.   Yes The United States is the biggest dog on the block  so we take most of the bad press anytime some country feels violated because god forbid they have not proven themselves responsible enough to be allowed nuclear capability.   Ill be the first to grant you that the U.S.A.  has done things we may or may not know about that were self motivated and not just for the greater good of the whole world (protecting Kuwait to keep our gas prices down).   However,  anytime there is an atrocity going on in the world (such as the slaughter that was going on in Yugoslavia/Bosnia)  the U.S.  is who everyone runs too asking for help.   <br>
<br>
     Anyway, I look forward to another patronizing response from you merton trying to rationalize why no country has a right to protest another country being able to incinerate the planet because all  soveriegn nations have the right to &quot;protect&quot; themselves with whatever weapons they wish to build.  I guess we arent trying to PROTECT ourselves by keeping nuclear bombs out of insane mens hands.   Enjoy whatever piece of socialist newsprint you read today while enjoying the freedom of living in the U.S. <p>&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;center&gt;Bractos Bootstrap, &lt;br&gt;Warlord of the Tribunal&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47476&gt;Inspect me</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mertondraco>Merton Draco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fuck all of you</span><br>  Posts: 1844<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/28/02 1:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=298.topic&index=72>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>How can you justify allowing a country led by a madman, a man who during the war in 1991 lauched numerous missles arbitrarily into Israeal just to turn his invasion of kuwait into a holy war and get the other arab nations to support him? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
